'''Valentino Francisco Livramento''' (born 12 November 2002) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|full-back]] for {{English football updater|NewcastU}} club [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] and the [[England national football team|England national team]].

==Early life==
Born in [[Croydon]], [[Greater London]], Livramento joined [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] at under-9 level from local club Roundshaw.<ref name=Chelsea>{{cite web|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2021/08/02/livramento-joins-southampton|title=Livramento Joins Southampton|date=2 August 2021|accessdate=5 August 2021|website=chelseafc.com}}</ref><ref name="athletic">{{cite web |last=Sheldon |first=Dan |date=2 August 2021 |title=Southampton sign Chelsea teenager Tino Livramento on five-year deal |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4203593/2021/08/02/southampton-sign-chelsea-teenager-tino-livramento-on-five-year-deal/ |url-access=subscription |access-date=5 August 2021 |website=theathletic.com}}</ref><ref name=goal>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/tino-livramento-european-clubs-queuing-sign-chelsea-academy/158es7jsarh4c1ix0zhhq5lu2h|title=Tino Livramento: Why European clubs are queuing up to sign Chelsea's academy star|first=Nizaar|last=Kinsella|date=20 July 2021|accessdate=5 August 2021|website=goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/chelsea-2021-01-05-18yearold-rightback-tino-livramento-named-player-to-watch-by-the-athletic/|title=18-year-old right-back Tino Livramento named 'player to watch' by the Athletic|first=Divij|last=Kulkarni|website=tribuna.com|date=5 January 2021|access-date=5 August 2021}}</ref> At Roundshaw he played as a striker.<ref name="BBC 59300180">{{cite web |last1=Rose |first1=Gary |title=Tino Livramento: Southampton defender aiming to upstage Liverpool's flying full-backs |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59300180 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=26 November 2021 |date=26 November 2021}}</ref> Growing up, he supported Chelsea.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=https://www.southamptonfc.com/news/2021-08-03/in-profile-tino-livramento-southampton-football-club-3-august-2021|title=In Profile: Tino Livramento|date=3 August 2021|accessdate=5 August 2021|website=southamptonfc.com}}</ref> His father's side of the family comes from Portugal<ref>{{cite web|date=11 April 2020|title=Teenage Kicks: Tino Livramento|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2020/04/09/teenage-kicks--tino-livramento|website=chelseafc.com|accessdate=5 August 2021}}</ref> and his mother is Scottish.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/scotland-could-land-another-full-25173663 |title=Scotland could land ANOTHER full back as Southampton star's mum tells him to ditch England |first=Robbie |last=Copeland |newspaper=Daily Record |date=8 October 2021 |accessdate=8 October 2021}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Chelsea===
Livramento was named Chelsea academy player of the year for the 2020–21 season.<ref name="academy">{{cite news |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/livramento-named-chelsea-academy-player-of-the-season|title=Livramento named Chelsea Academy Player of the Season|website=chelseafc.com|date=19 May 2021|access-date=5 August 2021}}</ref> Towards the end of the season, he featured on the bench in Premier League fixtures against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football.london/chelsea-fc/news/who-is-tino-livramento-chelsea-20556092|title=Who is Tino Livramento? Meet the rampaging wing-back on the bench for Chelsea vs Man City|first=Adam|last=Newson|date=8 May 2021|accessdate=5 August 2021|website=football.london}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=3 August 2021 |title=Southampton sign defender Tino Livramento from Chelsea |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/southampton-premier-league-england-arsenal-manchester-city-b1895426.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220621/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/southampton-premier-league-england-arsenal-manchester-city-b1895426.html |archive-date=21 June 2022 |accessdate=5 August 2021 |website=independent.co.uk}}</ref>

In July 2021, contract talks between Chelsea and Livramento stalled, with rumours that the wing-back was set to leave the club.<ref name=goal/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.caughtoffside.com/2021/07/13/chelsea-starlet-tino-livramento-stalling-over-new-contract/|title=Concern for Chelsea as promising youngster stalls over signing contract extension|first=Michael|last=Alvarado|date=13 July 2021|accessdate=5 August 2021|website=caughtoffside.com}}</ref> He was reportedly subject to interest from a host of English clubs, including [[Southern England#Football|South Coast]] rivals [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] and [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]], as well as [[AC Milan]] and [[RB Leipzig]].<ref name=goal/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/brighton-make-final-push-to-sign-chelseas-livramento-as-bate/87hk94r1yya51q27xn69fkssj|title=Brighton make final push to sign Chelsea's Livramento as Bate agrees £1.5m move to Leeds|first=Nizaar|last=Kinsella|date=22 July 2021|accessdate=5 August 2021|website=goal.com}}</ref>

===Southampton===
Having failed to reach an agreement with Chelsea, Livramento signed for fellow [[Premier League]] side [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] in August 2021, with a reported buy-back and sell-on clauses included.<ref name=athletic/> On 14 August 2021, Livramento made his first Premier League appearance for Southampton in a 3–1 defeat to [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=14 August 2021|title=Everton 3–1 Southampton|url=https://www.southamptonfc.com/news/2021-08-14/match-report-everton-southampton-premier-league-202122|access-date=16 August 2021|website=Southampton FC}}</ref> On 23 October 2021, Livramento scored his first professional goal in Southampton's 2–2 draw with [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Mann|first=Mantej|date=23 October 2021|title=Southampton 2–2 Burnley|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58936302|access-date=23 October 2021|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 24 April 2022, Livramento was ruled out for the remainder of 2022 following an [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|ACL injury]] during Southampton's 2–2 draw with Brighton.<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 April 2022 |title=Tino Livramento: Southampton confirm defender 'likely' to miss rest of 2022 after suffering serious knee injury at Brighton |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11700/12599949/tino-livramento-southampton-confirm-defender-likely-to-miss-rest-of-2022-after-suffering-serious-knee-injury-at-brighton |access-date=9 January 2023 |website=Sky Sports}}</ref>

On 21 May 2023, Livramento made his first appearance for Southampton in 392 days during a 3–1 defeat to Brighton, replacing [[James Bree (footballer)|James Bree]] in the 77th minute.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Garrick |first=Omar |date=21 May 2023 |title=Tino Livramento makes first Southampton appearance in 392 days with Brighton cameo |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4538428/2023/05/21/tino-livramento-southampton-brighton/ |url-access=subscription |access-date=22 May 2023 |website=The Athletic}}</ref>

===Newcastle United===
On 8 August 2023, Livramento joined [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]], signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=Newcastle United sign Valentino Livramento |url=https://www.nufc.co.uk/news/latest-news/newcastle-united-sign-valentino-livramento/ |website=www.nufc.co.uk |access-date=8 August 2023 |date=8 August 2023}}</ref> Although the fee was officially undisclosed, it was reported to be worth an initial £32&nbsp;million, plus £8&nbsp;million in add-ons.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tino Livramento: Newcastle sign Southampton defender in £40m deal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66397191 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=8 August 2023 |date=8 August 2023}}</ref> Livramento made his debut for Newcastle in a 1–0 defeat against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in the Premier League.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66482703|title=Man City 1–0 Newcastle: Julian Alvarez goal gives defending champions victory|first=Chris|last=Bevan|website=BBC Sport|date=19 August 2023|access-date=4 March 2024}}</ref> He made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut against [[Borussia Dortmund]], starting Newcastle's final 3 group stage matches, however they were unable to progress from their group.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newcastleunited.com/en/news/borussia-dortmund-2-newcastle-united-0|publisher=Newcastle United F.C.|title=Match Report: Borussia Dortmund 2 Newcastle United 0|date=7 November 2023|access-date=4 March 2024}}</ref>

In March 2024 Livramento scored his first goal for the club in a 3–0 victory against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]], running the length of the pitch before poking it under the [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68389646|title=Newcastle 3–0 Wolves: Alexander Isak, Anthony Gordon & Tino Livramento secure home win|first=Matthew|last=Howarth|website=BBC Sport|date=2 March 2024|access-date=4 March 2024}}</ref> He started in the [[2025 EFL Cup final]] as Newcastle defeated [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] to win their first domestic trophy for seventy years.<ref name="EFL">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c62zl58dg8qt#Line-ups|title=Liverpool 1–2 Newcastle United: Line-ups|first=Phil|last=McNulty|publisher=BBC Sport|date=16 March 2025|access-date=16 March 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Despite Livramento representing England through the youth ranks up to Under-21 level, he was also eligible to play for the Scotland and Portugal national teams through his mother being Scottish and his father being Portuguese.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/19486292.saints-new-signing-ex-chelsea-tino-livramento/|title=Who is Saints' new signing ex-Chelsea Tino Livramento?|first=Alfie|last=House|date=2 August 2021|accessdate=5 August 2021|website=dailyecho.co.uk}}</ref>{{Failed verification|date=July 2024}}

On 27 August 2021, Livramento received his first call up for the [[England national under-21 football team|England U21s]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2021/Aug/27/20212708-england-mu21s-squad-named-for-romania-and-kosovo-in-september|title=Carsley names first MU21s squad|first=Nicholas|last=Veevers|website=EnglandFootball.com|date=27 August 2021|access-date=27 August 2021}}</ref> On 7 September 2021, he made his England U21 debut during the 2–0 [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification]] win over [[Kosovo national under-21 football team|Kosovo U21s]] at [[Stadium MK]].<ref>{{cite news|title=England U21 2–0 Kosovo U21|work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58460993|date=7 September 2021|access-date=7 September 2021}}</ref>

On 29 August 2024, Livramento was called up to the [[England national football team|England senior squad]] for the first time for [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League]] matches against [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]] and [[Finland national football team|Finland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c985q16jrn4o|title=Gomes, Livramento and Madueke in England squad|website=BBC Sport|date=29 August 2024|accessdate=29 August 2024}}</ref> He made his senior debut on 17 November 2024 in a 5–0 victory against the Republic of Ireland.<ref>{{cite web |last1=McNulty |first1=Phil |title=England 5–0 Republic of Ireland: Hosts score five in second half to earn Nations League promotion |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c98envjpj72t |website=BBC Sport |access-date=17 November 2024 |date=17 November 2024}}</ref>

Livramento was included in the England squad for the [[2025 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]] which was the only international youth tournament he ever attended.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c5y21xdz703o|title=Livramento has 'beautiful future' – but could he make World Cup squad?|first=Alex|last=Howell|publisher=BBC Sport|date=14 June 2025|access-date=2 July 2025}}</ref> He started in the quarter-final victory over [[Spain national under-21 football team|Spain]] and semi-final win against [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cp86mjyr58dt|title=England U21 3–1 Spain U21|first=Nick|last=Mashiter|publisher=BBC Sport|date=21 June 2025|access-date=2 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c39z0ekwnd0t|title=England U21 2–1 Netherlands U21|first=Nick|last=Mashiter|publisher=BBC Sport|date=25 June 2025|access-date=2 July 2025}}</ref> Livramento then played every minute of the [[2025 UEFA European Under-21 Championship final|final]] as England defeated [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany]] after extra time to lift the trophy.<ref name="U21">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cz6g18dz2dpt|title=England U-21 3 Germany U-21 2|first=Nick|last=Mashiter|publisher=BBC Sport|date=28 June 2025|access-date=29 June 2025}}</ref> His performances during the competition resulted in him being chosen by the UEFA Technical Observer panel for their team of the tournament.<ref name="tott">{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/news/029b-1e218d6c7f6f-b542bb91eb18-1000--2025-under-21-euro-team-of-the-tournament/|title=2025 Under-21 EURO Team of the Tournament|newspaper=UEFA|date=1 July 2025|access-date=2 July 2025}}</ref>

